  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA232-kiḷavi">itu pakal vantāṉai “iravu vā” veṉat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante said to the one who came by day “come by night!”</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA232">
<l>            ciṟukaṇ yāṉaip peruṅkai yīriṉaṅ</l>
<l>            kuḷavit taṇkayaṅ kuḻaiyat tīṇṭic</l>
<l>            cōlai vāḻai muṇaii yayalatu</l>
<l>            vēral vēlic ciṟukuṭi yalaṟac</l>
<l>            ceṅkāṟ palaviṉ ṟīmpaḻa micaiyu </l>
<l>            māmalai nāṭa tāma nalkeṉa</l>
<l>            vēṇṭutum vāḻiya ventai vēṅkai</l>
<l>            vīyuka virinta muṉṟiṟ</l>
<l>            kalkeḻu pākkat talkiṉai celiṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from the land of great mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the large-trunked pair of small-eyed elephants,</l>
<l rend="indent2">after taking, until they are tired, possession of the cool pond</l>
<l rend="indent3">with wild jasmine, dislike the bananas in the grove</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] taste the sweet fruit of the red-trunked jack-tree,</l>
<l rend="indent4">so that the small bamboo-fenced hamlet cries out, 	</l>
<l rend="indent4">in the neighbourhood,</l>
<l>– we entreat [you], may you live, to grant [us your] string(?)<note place="foot">What may be the implication of this request? And what actually is <term xml:lang="ta">tāmam</term>, not at all a familiar word?</note>,</l>
<l>you who have abided in the stony village in the front yard</l>
<l rend="indent2">spread with blossoms shed by the Vēṅkai tree of my father,</l>
<l rend="indent4">when you go.<note place="foot">Here <term xml:lang="ta">alkiṉai</term> is best understood as the sort of <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term> ("when you go after having abided..."), that is used to express temporal anteriority in the action of a sub-clause.</note></l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
